In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Kayleigh McEnany condemned the violence that took place at the Capitol building on January 6, 2021. She described the actions as appalling and antithetical to the American way. McEnany emphasized that the Trump administration strongly condemns the violence and believes that those who broke the law should be prosecuted to the fullest extent. She expressed condolences for the loss of life and injuries and thanked law enforcement officers for their efforts. McEnany stated that the actions of the violent rioters undermined the legitimate rights of peaceful protesters and went against the core values of the administration, which prioritize safety, peace, and freedom for all citizens. She called for unity and the rejection of violence, emphasizing that America is one nation under God.